---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Collection">
  <section class="container-narrow py-16 max-w-3xl">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-8">About the Collection</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-charcoal">
      <p class="text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed text-lg">
        This collection represents a personal journey through human history, assembled over years of careful curation. Each piece tells a story—of ancient empires, skilled craftsmen, and the enduring human desire to create objects of beauty and meaning.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">Areas of Focus</h2>

      <p class="text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed">
        The collection spans several categories, each chosen for their historical significance and artistic merit:
      </p>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-charcoal/80">
        <li><strong>Ancient Coins</strong> — Greek, Roman, Byzantine, and Near Eastern coinage</li>
        <li><strong>Cylinder Seals</strong> — Mesopotamian administrative and artistic objects</li>
        <li><strong>Jewelry & Rings</strong> — Wearable art from various periods and cultures</li>
        <li><strong>Small Antiques</strong> — Curios and objects of historical interest</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">Philosophy</h2>

      <p class="text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed">
        Quality over quantity guides every acquisition. Each item must meet strict criteria for authenticity, condition, and historical importance. Provenance and legal acquisition are paramount—every piece in this collection has been ethically sourced and can be traced to legitimate dealers and auction houses.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">Contact</h2>

      <p class="text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed">
        For inquiries about the collection, please reach out via email.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
